<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-16T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="225" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2172: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-16T18:00:00+01:00">October 16, 1931—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 16—1:25 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>209. Consulate’s 208, October 16, 6 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] p.m.
                            Council met at 6 p.m. and I delivered statement. I understand that you
                            are releasing in Washington.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>